Yes — here’s a clean framework version of the Webflow AEO maturity model, stripped down into something you can use for Crossfuze.

AEO Maturity Framework
The model is built on 4 dimensions and 5 maturity stages. The dimensions are Content, Technical, Authority, and Measurement. The maturity journey moves from basic SEO-style visibility toward AI-ready, authority-led visibility in answer engines. 

The 4 dimensions
Content
Move from keyword-led pages to genuinely useful, question-led answers that cover the topics buyers actually care about. At higher maturity, content becomes broader, fresher, and more tailored to segment, persona, or use case. 

Technical
Make the site easy for AI systems to interpret. That means strong structure, schema markup, fast performance, clean page hierarchy, and scalable implementation across the site. 

Authority
Shift from relying mainly on backlinks to becoming a trusted source across the web. This includes credible mentions, thought leadership, expert content, and presence in places AI systems often draw from, such as industry publications, forums, video, and community platforms. 

Measurement
Move beyond keyword rankings and organic traffic alone. Track how often your brand appears in AI-generated answers, how you compare with competitors, and whether visibility is improving for the questions that matter most. 

The 5 maturity stages
Level 1 — Keywords
Basic visibility built mainly around brand terms and core category keywords. Good for known demand, weak for broader AI discovery. 

Level 2 — Answers
Content starts answering real buyer questions rather than just targeting keywords. This expands reach into earlier-stage discovery. 

Level 3 — Structure
Answers are now supported by clearer site structure, stronger organization, and AI-friendly formatting so systems can understand meaning more reliably. 

Level 4 — Pillar
The brand becomes a recognised source in its category. Authority grows, citations increase, and visibility compounds. 

Level 5 — Authority
AEO becomes continuous and scalable. Content, structure, authority, and measurement are operating systematically and adapting as answer engines evolve. 

Simplified executive version
For a CRO or board audience, I’d compress it to this:

Stage	What it means
1. Keyword Visible	Brand shows up mainly for direct or obvious searches
2. Answer Ready	Content answers real prospect questions
3. AI Structured	Site and content are machine-readable and easy for AI to interpret
4. AI Recognised	Brand is increasingly cited and trusted in AI answers
5. AI Authority	Brand consistently owns category visibility across AI discovery
This is a simplification of Webflow’s original five stages — Keywords, Answers, Structure, Pillar, Authority — reworded for executive clarity. 

Crossfuze version
For Crossfuze, the practical framework could be:

1. Invisible — little to no AI visibility
2. Unstructured — content exists but AI struggles to interpret it
3. AI Structured — schema, page structure, and service clarity are in place
4. AI Cited — Crossfuze is referenced in AI-generated answers
5. AI Authority — Crossfuze is a recognised ServiceNow source across AI discovery

That is not Webflow’s exact naming, but it is a sensible adaptation of their framework for your board reporting and AEO roadmap. 

