1. HTTPS Enforcement (Security & Trust)

We verified that the website is fully served over HTTPS and that all non-secure versions of the site automatically redirect to the secure version.

Why this matters

HTTPS is a baseline ranking and trust signal used by search engines.

It also:

Prevents duplicate indexing of secure vs non-secure page versions

Ensures user data protection and browser trust signals

Provides a consistent and secure user experience across the site

Outcome

All site variants (http, https, www, and non-www) now resolve to a single secure destination.

2. URL Canonicalisation (Single Source of Truth)

A canonical tag was implemented and validated to ensure search engines recognise the preferred version of the Crossfuze website.

Canonical URL

https://www.crossfuze.com/

Why this matters

Canonicalisation prevents search engines from interpreting multiple URL variations as separate pages.

This:

Prevents duplicate content issues

Consolidates SEO authority and link equity into a single page version

Ensures search engines and AI systems reference the correct page

Outcome

Search engines now receive a clear signal that the HTTPS www domain is the authoritative version of the Crossfuze website.

3. Structured Data – Organisation & Website Entity Definition

Global Schema.org structured data was implemented across the site to explicitly define Crossfuze as an organisation and associate the website, logo, and brand identity with that entity.

